          "question": "Does my loved one's spouse's income count toward the limit?",
          "answer": "Yes, the 125% poverty level limit applies to total family income, including your loved one's spouse. For a 2-person household in 2025, the limit is approximately $26,397 annually. Contact your local provider to verify current thresholds for your specific household size."
